    <note type="biography">
        <p>Naval medical officer and biologist. Trained at Cork school of medicine and King’s College, London. Entered the navy as assistant surgeon in 1849. Served on the <hi rend="italic">Herald</hi>, 1852–9. Professor of naval hygiene, Netley, 1872. Deputy inspector general, 1875; inspector general, 1880. Head, Royal Naval Hospital, Plymouth, 1883–6. FRS 1859.</p></note>
